How can I add Drill Down functionality to a Map visualization in Power BI Desktop?

When you have created a hierarchy you can use that hierarchy to create a drill-down on the map.

The highlighted yellow box in the image below allows you to activate the drill down functionality. This appears by selecting the Map visualization and appears at the top right corner of the map.




Click on the arrow pointing down and it will appear marked.




Now that the drill down is activated, you can hover over a data point and click on it and will deliver the drill down feature.

The image below shows the result of the Maryland data point drill down.




Hovering over a data point gives you specific data for each city in the state.








To recover to the original map visualization, click the up arrow that is the “Drill Up.”






https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/power-bi/consumer/end-user-drill How can I add Drill Down functionality to a Map visualization in Power BI Desktop?
